The Zamfara State Police Command has confirmed the killing of the son of the state Commissioner of Security and Internal Affairs, Hon. Ibrahim Mamnan Tsafe and others by bandits. This is just as the state’s Commissioner of Police, Mr. Ibrahim Ayuba Elkanah, has visited Tsafe town to commiserate with families of the victims. Elkanah said the reason for his visit was to assess the existing security emplacement of the area with a view to deploying additional reinforcement that would forestall future attacks in Tsafe and its environs. While at Tsafe town, the commissioner condoled with the Commissioner for Security and Home Affairs, Rtd DIG Mamman Ibrahim Tsafe and families of other victims that lost their three sons in the attack. DAILY POST reports that the incident occured while people were observing Isha’i prayers when suspected armed bandits on motorcycles stormed the area from eastern outskirt, shooting sporadically. It was also gathered that joint police and other security operatives have been mobilized to the scene and engaged the assailants in a serious gun battle that forced them to retreat to the bush. Three persons including the son of Commissioner for Security and Home Affair (Rtd)DIG Mamman Ibrahim Tsafe were shot dead by the bandits. The Police Commissioner further directed the State CID to conduct a discreet investigation with a view to unravelling the circumstances surrounding the attacks.